if you wish to reproduce this project the falowing hardware list may be of assistance.

board: Raspberry Pi Zero 2w
thermocouple amp: MAX 31855
roaster: popper gen 2
dac: MCP4728


Popper coffee roaster
https://www.sweetmarias.com/collections/popper/products/popper
Grey 2025 / 3rd production-run Popper
7 numbered stepped heat levels
Improved fan motor
Built-in 7 minute roast + 3 minute cooldown cycle


Raspberry Pi Zero 2w
https://www.raspberrypi.com/products/raspberry-pi-zero-2-w/
Hostname: RoastPi
Runs the control service
Creates the PopperRoaster Wi-Fi network

Thermocouple
https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07PMW21N2/?coliid=I3G5PRXYIT1K3L&colid=2AOLKRJ0U7HFS&psc=1&ref

MAX31855 thermocouple amplifier
https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CNXHQFWX/?coliid=I12BZOCLBNF8SK&colid=2AOLKRJ0U7HFS&psc=1&ref
Reads bean temperature
Uses SPI
SPI device: /dev/spidev0.0
Code uses SPI bus 0, device 0
Speed: 5,000,000 Hz


MCP4728 DAC
https://www.amazon.com/dp/B09FF5J5WJ/?coliid=I2VB530UP3G7YW&colid=2AOLKRJ0U7HFS&psc=1&ref
I2C address: 0x60
I2C bus: 1
Reference voltage: 5.0 V
DAC Channel B / channel 1: heat output


5v power suply for Raspberry Pi

32GB micro sd card
https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00M55C0NS/?coliid=IEUPNZBTT64CH&colid=2AOLKRJ0U7HFS&ref


Notes: If the thermocouple amplifier board is too close to the Pi, the Wi-Fi antenna will cause interference in your temperature readings.
